wmisdnmon-0.9b - Public BETA release
--------------------------------------------------------------
Authors...: Marcelo Morgade (marcelomorgade@ig.com.br)
		

Description
--------------------------------------------------------------
wmisdnmon logs the 5 latest calls for your ISDN line. Click in
a number logged to see details about calls. It use the 
isdninfo daemon distributed with kisdnmon (a similar 
application for kde). You must install i4ldaemons set the 
init.d to initialize it. wmisdnmon use only the isdninfo daemon
(you can disable i4lmon for security purposes).
If you have a sound card and installed the sox package, you 
will listen a ring when there is a incoming call.

wmisdnmon is being developped on a machine running 
Conectiva Linux 7.0 (Brazilian RedHat like distro)

